originalText.text:
I visited this place once. It wasn’t my fault. I simply saw a small fire and immediately took action at an Italian restaurant nearby. With a whimsical leap from my chair, and a mere slight of hand, I was able to extinguish a dinner menu that had been set aflame by a careless busboy. I didn’t even remember what he looked like, but having explained the simple incident to the restauranteur just moments after I basically saved the establishment and all the patrons enjoying their meals, I witnessed the swift dismissal of the busboy by said restauranteur right out on in front of all the customers.

Well, needless to say, I felt so bad about this, but luckily my dear friend was able to acquire the busboy’s home address, and I decided to visit him to apologize and explain that I had no intention of getting him in any trouble.
Luckily another good friend of mine (I actually have 3 very good friends and we often exchange favors), accompanied me to visit this young man. I recall he had a cat, and my friend “accidentally” left this man’s apartment door wide open, allowing his cat to escape. Anyway, it’s a long story; one you’ve probably heard before, but in the end, my life was as mediocre as before the incident ever took place, and I never heard from that busboy again.
Oh, and the apartment is kinda small, probably not worth the rent there, and hopefully they corrected the paint job (See photo showing the door). Good luck, and if you visit this home, just tell them Cantstandya sentya!!
